New Records: De'Aaron Fox moved to second place in most steals in Kings history with his 671st career steal.
Key Match Events: De'Aaron Fox finished with 19 points, six assists, five rebounds, and one steal.
Domantas Sabonis finished with a game-high 28 points, 11 rebounds, and four assists.
DeMar DeRozan added 20 points, eight assists, and four rebounds.
Jordan Clarkson led the Jazz with 21 points.
Post-Match Reflections: De'Aaron Fox talked about playing with desperation to avoid starting the season 0-3.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Kings held the Jazz to 14 third-quarter points en route to their first 15+ point win of the season.
